            "content": "SBA 504 Loans: Government-backed loans for property improvements. Lower rates than conventional financing (typically 3%-5% fixed for 10-25 years), longer terms reducing monthly payments, requires 10% down payment, and typically 30-60 day approval process. Best for businesses making substantial building improvements beyond just roofing. PACE Financing (Property Assessed Clean Energy): Special financing for energy-efficient commercial roofing. Repaid through property tax assessment over 15-25 years, remains with property if sold, no personal guarantee required, and covers 100% of project cost for qualifying energy improvements. Requires cool roof installation and insulation upgrades meeting efficiency standards. Rates typically 6%-8% but extended terms lower payments. Example: $250,000 roof replacement through PACE at 6.5% over 20 years = $1,867/month payment added to property taxes. Cash Payment with Utility Rebates: Some businesses choose cash payment capturing maximum rebates and incentives. Tucson Electric Power and Southwest Gas offer commercial rebates for cool roof installations and increased insulation—typically $0.10-$0.50 per square foot. Federal tax deductions under Section 179D allow immediate expensing of energy-efficient building improvements including roofing—potentially $1.80+ per square foot in tax benefits. We help businesses navigate available incentives providing necessary documentation and certifications."
