            "content": "Commercial roof replacement costs vary significantly based on building size, existing roof condition, membrane system selected, insulation R-value, and project complexity. Typical Tucson commercial roof replacement costs: Value TPO System (45-mil membrane, R-20 insulation, 15-year warranty): $4.50-$5.50 per square foot installed. Best for buildings with limited budgets or shorter ownership horizons. Standard EPDM or TPO (60-mil membrane, R-25 insulation, 20-year warranty): $5.50-$6.75 per square foot installed. Most popular option balancing cost, performance, and warranty coverage. Premium PVC System (80-mil membrane, R-30-R35 insulation, 25-30 year warranty): $7.00-$9.00 per square foot installed. Best for buildings prioritizing maximum service life, energy efficiency, and warranty protection. Additional costs may include deck repairs ($8-$15 per SF for damaged areas), drainage improvements ($350-$800 per new drain), parapet and flashing upgrades ($25-$45 per linear foot), roof-mounted equipment curb replacement ($450-$1,200 per unit), and engineering for complex projects ($2,500-$8,500). Always request detailed written proposals outlining all costs, payment terms, and what's included versus optional items."
